<section class="py-24 px-6 border-t border-theme-border">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_1px_240px] gap-0 items-start">

      <!-- Story -->
      <div class="story-col">
        <p class="section-label">How this started</p>

        <div class="story-blocks">
          <p>
            I started using Claude Code on day one. Pretty quickly I was hacking together tmux scripts to run multiple agents in parallel, one on the frontend, one on the backend, just to see if I could get them to coordinate. It worked, sort of. But finding old conversations was painful, setup disappeared every time my machine restarted, and orphan MCP processes would silently eat RAM and CPU in the background.
          </p>

          <p>
            So I put together a small web app. Just a place to chat, search, and keep things organised. That was the whole idea.
          </p>

          <p>
            Then I started working across multiple projects and needed <strong>context isolation</strong>. A way to switch mental contexts without juggling random windows. I didn't want to reopen everything after a restart. I wanted a persistent interface that just picks up where I left off. One app, one state, no wasted memory from duplicate processes.
          </p>

          <p>
            I knew from the start that Anthropic and OpenAI would ship their own versions of this, and they did. But I was also sure those products would be built for the general public, not for someone like me who needs to orchestrate agents across repos every day. <strong>This is built for the workflow I actually have.</strong>
          </p>

          <p>
            I use Molt Code daily across different projects. I'm building the next version of this app inside this app. It's sticking around because I need it, and I'll keep improving it for as long as that's true.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Vertical rule -->
      <div class="vr"></div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <div class="side-col">
        <div class="side-block">
          <p class="side-kicker">Today</p>
          <p class="side-value">Used daily</p>
          <p class="side-sub">across multiple projects</p>
        </div>

        <div class="side-block">
          <p class="side-value">Self-hosted</p>
          <p class="side-sub">Building v.next inside itself</p>
        </div>

        <div class="side-bugs">
          <p>You <em>will</em> find bugs. This is early. When you do, please open an issue.</p>
